{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"name":"ir","display_name":"R","language":"R"},"language_info":{"name":"R","codemirror_mode":"r","pygments_lexer":"r","mimetype":"text/x-r-source","file_extension":".r","version":"4.0.5"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[],"dockerImageVersionId":30618,"isInternetEnabled":true,"language":"r","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"source":"<a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/code/sanghyuni/r-basic-2?scriptVersionId=165128066\" target=\"_blank\"><img align=\"left\" alt=\"Kaggle\" title=\"Open in Kaggle\" src=\"https://kaggle.com/static/images/open-in-kaggle.svg\"></a>","metadata":{},"cell_type":"markdown"},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# This R environment comes with many helpful analytics packages installed\n# It is defined by the kaggle/rstats Docker image: https://github.com/kaggle/docker-rstats\n# For example, here's a helpful package to load\n\nlibrary(tidyverse) # metapackage of all tidyverse packages\n\n# Input data files are available in the read-only \"../input/\" directory\n# For example, running this (by clicking run or pressing Shift+Enter) will list all files under the input directory\n\nlist.files(path = \"../input\")\n\n# You can write up to 20GB to the current directory (/kaggle/working/) that gets preserved as output when you create a version using \"Save & Run All\" \n# You can also write temporary files to /kaggle/temp/, but they won't be saved outside of the current session","metadata":{"_uuid":"051d70d956493feee0c6d64651c6a088724dca2a","_execution_state":"idle","execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T10:05:52.308127Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T10:05:52.311145Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T10:05:53.909165Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":1,"outputs":[{"name":"stderr","text":"── \u001b[1mAttaching core tidyverse packages\u001b[22m ──────────────────────── tidyverse 2.0.0 ──\n\u001b[32m✔\u001b[39m \u001b[34mdplyr    \u001b[39m 1.1.4     \u001b[32m✔\u001b[39m \u001b[34mreadr    \u001b[39m 2.1.4\n\u001b[32m✔\u001b[39m \u001b[34mforcats  \u001b[39m 1.0.0     \u001b[32m✔\u001b[39m \u001b[34mstringr  \u001b[39m 1.5.1\n\u001b[32m✔\u001b[39m \u001b[34mggplot2  \u001b[39m 3.4.4     \u001b[32m✔\u001b[39m \u001b[34mtibble   \u001b[39m 3.2.1\n\u001b[32m✔\u001b[39m \u001b[34mlubridate\u001b[39m 1.9.3     \u001b[32m✔\u001b[39m \u001b[34mtidyr    \u001b[39m 1.3.0\n\u001b[32m✔\u001b[39m \u001b[34mpurrr    \u001b[39m 1.0.2     \n── \u001b[1mConflicts\u001b[22m ────────────────────────────────────────── tidyverse_conflicts() ──\n\u001b[31m✖\u001b[39m \u001b[34mdplyr\u001b[39m::\u001b[32mfilter()\u001b[39m masks \u001b[34mstats\u001b[39m::filter()\n\u001b[31m✖\u001b[39m \u001b[34mdplyr\u001b[39m::\u001b[32mlag()\u001b[39m    masks \u001b[34mstats\u001b[39m::lag()\n\u001b[36mℹ\u001b[39m Use the conflicted package (\u001b[3m\u001b[34m<http://conflicted.r-lib.org/>\u001b[39m\u001b[23m) to force all conflicts to become errors\n","output_type":"stream"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/html":"","text/markdown":"","text/latex":"","text/plain":"character(0)"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## 1. Factor","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"review <- c(\"Good\", \"Indifferent\", \"Bad\", \"Good\", \"Bad\")\nreview_factor <- factor(review)\nreview_factor","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T07:51:47.627632Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T07:51:47.629637Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T07:51:47.657469Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"str(review_factor) # each factor has a level -> num\nas.numeric(review_factor)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T07:52:52.021199Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T07:52:52.023608Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T07:52:52.04852Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"event_day <- c(\"Mon\", \"Tue\", \"Wed\", \"Sat\", \"Fri\", \"Sat\")\nevent_day_factor <- factor(event_day)\nevent_day_factor\n\n# Use levels to set all of levels\nevent_day_factor <- factor(event_day, levels = c(\"Mon\", \"Tue\", \"Wed\", \"Thu\", \"Fri\", \"Sat\", \"Sun\")) # levels are ordered\nevent_day_factor","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T07:55:50.51142Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T07:55:50.51386Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T07:55:50.553344Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### GPT\n* 완전성: 모든 요일을 levels에 포함시킴으로써, 팩터가 나타내는 범주가 주 7일 모두를 포함하도록 합니다. 이는 분석에서 모든 요일을 고려하려는 경우에 중요할 수 있습니다, 심지어 데이터 세트에 특정 요일의 데이터가 없더라도 말이죠.\n\n* 순서 지정: 팩터는 기본적으로 범주형 데이터를 처리하는 데 사용되며, levels를 사용하면 이러한 범주의 순서를 명시적으로 지정할 수 있습니다. 이 경우 요일이 일반적으로 인식되는 순서대로 배열됩니다. 이 순서는 플롯, 요약 통계, 모델링 등에서 중요할 수 있습니다.\n\n* 결측 범주 처리: 데이터에 특정 요일이 누락되어 있더라도, 모든 요일을 levels에 포함시키면 해당 요일이 분석에 포함되고 결과 출력에 나타납니다. 예를 들어, 데이터 세트에 'Thu'나 'Sun'이 없다 하더라도, 이러한 요일은 결과적으로 생성된 팩터 레벨에 포함됩니다.\n\n* 일관성 유지: 데이터 분석에서 여러 데이터 세트를 다룰 때, 모든 데이터 세트에서 동일한 levels 설정을 사용하면 결과의 일관성을 유지할 수 있습니다. 이는 데이터를 병합하거나 비교할 때 특히 중요합니다.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"review_factor <- factor(review, levels = c(\"Good\", \"Bad\", \"Indifferent\"))\nreview_factor","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T07:58:19.4386Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T07:58:19.440691Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T07:58:19.468375Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Show the levels of factor\nlevels(event_day_factor)\nlevels(review_factor)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T07:57:25.612759Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T07:57:25.615076Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T07:57:25.644383Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# Change the levels\nlevels(review_factor) <- c(\"G\", \"I\", \"B\")\nreview_factor\ntable(review_factor)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T08:00:11.356656Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T08:00:11.358673Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T08:00:11.391353Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# example\nsur <-  c(\"Mid\", \"High\", \"Low\", \"Mid\", \"High\", \"Low\", \"Mid\", \"High\", \"Low\")\nsur_factor <- factor(sur)\nsur_factor\ntable(sur_factor)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T08:04:01.238316Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T08:04:01.2402Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T08:04:01.276027Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# set the order\nsur_factor_ <- factor(sur, levels = c(\"Low\", \"High\", \"Mid\"), ordered = TRUE)\nsur_factor_\ntable(sur_factor_)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T08:04:10.114932Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T08:04:10.117015Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T08:04:10.145354Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# example 2\nsex <- c(2, 1, 2, 1, 1, 2, 1, 1, 1, 2, 2, 0)\nsex_factor <- factor(sex, levels = c(1, 2), labels = c(\"Male\", \"Female\"))\nsex_factor\ntable(sex_factor)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T08:06:45.435346Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T08:06:45.437605Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T08:06:45.47347Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### About forcats library","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"food <- factor(c(\"Vegetables\", \"Fruits\", \"Meat\", \"Fruits\", \"Vegetables\", \"Meat\", \"Fruits\", \"Vegetables\", \"Meat\", \"Dairy\"\n  ,\"Fruits\"))\nfood","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T10:56:53.048707Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T10:56:53.102803Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T10:56:53.130881Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":2,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/html":"<style>\n.list-inline {list-style: none; margin:0; padding: 0}\n.list-inline>li {display: inline-block}\n.list-inline>li:not(:last-child)::after {content: \"\\00b7\"; padding: 0 .5ex}\n</style>\n<ol class=list-inline><li>Vegetables</li><li>Fruits</li><li>Meat</li><li>Fruits</li><li>Vegetables</li><li>Meat</li><li>Fruits</li><li>Vegetables</li><li>Meat</li><li>Dairy</li><li>Fruits</li></ol>\n\n<details>\n\t<summary style=display:list-item;cursor:pointer>\n\t\t<strong>Levels</strong>:\n\t</summary>\n\t<style>\n\t.list-inline {list-style: none; margin:0; padding: 0}\n\t.list-inline>li {display: inline-block}\n\t.list-inline>li:not(:last-child)::after {content: \"\\00b7\"; padding: 0 .5ex}\n\t</style>\n\t<ol class=list-inline><li>'Dairy'</li><li>'Fruits'</li><li>'Meat'</li><li>'Vegetables'</li></ol>\n</details>","text/markdown":"1. Vegetables\n2. Fruits\n3. Meat\n4. Fruits\n5. Vegetables\n6. Meat\n7. Fruits\n8. Vegetables\n9. Meat\n10. Dairy\n11. Fruits\n\n\n\n**Levels**: 1. 'Dairy'\n2. 'Fruits'\n3. 'Meat'\n4. 'Vegetables'\n\n\n","text/latex":"\\begin{enumerate*}\n\\item Vegetables\n\\item Fruits\n\\item Meat\n\\item Fruits\n\\item Vegetables\n\\item Meat\n\\item Fruits\n\\item Vegetables\n\\item Meat\n\\item Dairy\n\\item Fruits\n\\end{enumerate*}\n\n\\emph{Levels}: \\begin{enumerate*}\n\\item 'Dairy'\n\\item 'Fruits'\n\\item 'Meat'\n\\item 'Vegetables'\n\\end{enumerate*}\n","text/plain":" [1] Vegetables Fruits     Meat       Fruits     Vegetables Meat      \n [7] Fruits     Vegetables Meat       Dairy      Fruits    \nLevels: Dairy Fruits Meat Vegetables"},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"library(forcats)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T08:31:28.844079Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T08:31:28.846165Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T08:31:28.863581Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# by order\nfct_inorder(food) # view the levels in order of elements order\n\n# by fequency\nfct_infreq(food) # view the levels in order of frequency\n\n# reorder\nfct_relevel(food, \"Fruits\", \"Meat\", \"Vegetables\", \"Dairy\")\n\n#if you put single level, it will be the first level. other level will be in order of existing order\nfct_relevel(food, \"Meat\")\nfct_relevel(food, \"Meat\", \"Fruits\")\nfct_relevel(food, \"Meat\", after = 2)\nfct_relevel(food, \"Meat\", \"Fruits\", after = 2)\n#fct_relevel(food, \"Meat\", \"Fruits\", after = \"Vegteables\")\nfct_relevel(food, \"Meat\", after= Inf) # last level","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2024-03-02T10:56:57.582487Z","iopub.execute_input":"2024-03-02T10:56:57.584558Z","iopub.status.idle":"2024-03-02T10:56:57.664028Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":3,"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/html":"<style>\n.list-inline {list-style: none; margin:0; padding: 0}\n.list-inline>li {display: inline-block}\n.list-inline>li:not(:last-child)::after {content: \"\\00b7\"; padding: 0 .5ex}\n</style>\n<ol class=list-inline><li>Vegetables</li><li>Fruits</li><li>Meat</li><li>Fruits</li><li>Vegetables</li><li>Meat</li><li>Fruits</li><li>Vegetables</li><li>Meat</li><li>Dairy</li><li>Fruits</li></ol>\n\n<details>\n\t<summary style=display:list-item;cursor:pointer>\n\t\t<strong>Levels</strong>:\n\t</summary>\n\t<style>\n\t.list-inline {list-style: none; margin:0; padding: 0}\n\t.list-inline>li {display: inline-block}\n\t.list-inline>li:not(:last-child)::after {content: \"\\00b7\"; padding: 0 .5ex}\n\t</style>\n\t<ol class=list-inline><li>'Vegetables'</li><li>'Fruits'</li><li>'Meat'</li><li>'Dairy'</li></ol>\n</details>","text/markdown":"1. Vegetables\n2. Fruits\n3. Meat\n4. Fruits\n5. Vegetables\n6. Meat\n7. Fruits\n8. Vegetables\n9. Meat\n10. Dairy\n11. Fruits\n\n\n\n**Levels**: 1. 'Vegetables'\n2. 'Fruits'\n3. 'Meat'\n4. 'Dairy'\n\n\n","text/latex":"\\begin{enumerate*}\n\\item Vegetables\n\\item Fruits\n\\item Meat\n\\item Fruits\n\\item Vegetables\n\\item Meat\n\\item Fruits\n\\item Vegetables\n\\item Mea